  "text": "Rocca (2010) believes that there are many ways to motivate students to participate actively, such as controlling the class size, dividing the students into groups, placing the student seats in U-shaped or circular, and counting participation as part of a student's grade. In addition, instructors play a key role in motivating students to participate. Instructors should respect students, pay attention to students' views and praise students when appropriate. At the same time, instructors can create supportive climates by knowing students' names (Nunn, 1996; [CITATION_1] , showing interest and support for students' participation through eye contact and smiles, giving students verbal and nonverbal feedback (Nadler, 1990 ",
